<h3>4.3.9 Notification Hub</h3>
<p>A specific operational view facilitating modifications upon designated HTML-styled text strings formulating systemic outbound email structures. Administrators directly format templates individually pushing manual or bulk dispatches explicitly targeted towards database subsets independently bypassing external platforms.</p>
<span class="image-message">[Insert Image: Notice Control Hub]</span>

<h3>4.3.10 Special Implementations</h3>
<p><strong>Frontend and Backend Validation:</strong> Every data entry form in the Customer and Admin interfaces uses standard validators for real-time inline error feedback before any API request is made. Enforced rules include required field checks, valid phone number digits, and password complexity. On the backend, controllers validate incoming request bodies containing business logic restrictions tracking quantities and delivery date validity. Database layer validations enforce strict data types preventing relational orphan faults.</p>
<p><strong>Security and Encryption:</strong> Passwords are hashed with Bcryptjs using 10 salt rounds; plaintext passwords are never logged at any point in the system. JWT tokens are verified securely processing hidden signatures. All API keys and database URLs are isolated in server-side `.env` packages securely excluded from operational version control channels naturally protecting system architectures.</p>
<p><strong>Error Handling:</strong> A global Express error handling middleware sits at the end of the middleware chain catching all unhandled execution exceptions returning strictly normalized JSON variables mapped properly towards standard client HTTP responses (404, 500) simultaneously logging stack-traces internally mitigating exposure mapping towards arbitrary client screens completely bypassing silent operational failures effectively.</p>

<h2>4.4 Quality Assurance Methods Used</h2>
<p>Quality assurance was conducted continuously throughout development. Validation testing covered every data entry form with deliberate invalid inputs verifying that each returned the correct red inline error boundaries prior to backend submission. Error injection testing purposefully fed expired JWT tokens tracking whether authentication middlewares correctly expelled sessions appropriately reacting strictly protecting authorized routes effectively.</p>
<p>Manual end-to-end testing followed the complete operational lifecycle tracing account generation propagating sequential variants checking out submitting demo payment visual deposits verifying exact replication translating seamlessly directly onto administrative verification tables evaluating administrative actions transitioning states successfully ultimately concluding at confirmed deliveries confirming holistic parity spanning both isolated systems independently guaranteeing the complete operational viability extensively.</p>

<h2>4.5 Key Libraries and Justification</h2>
<p>Library selection was driven by specific technical requirements mitigating manual development configurations. <strong>Prisma</strong> superseded native SQL executions granting dynamic compile-time safety explicitly preventing silent field mismatches entirely. <strong>Bcryptjs</strong> executes adaptive architectural capabilities hashing variables effectively rendering database compromises computationally worthless. <strong>Nodemailer</strong> guarantees internal systemic SMTP connectivity pushing required transaction data instantaneously parsing variable components effectively. <strong>Ant Design</strong> practically eliminated UI generation times directly supplying enterprise-ready modals processing standardized tables extensively accelerating the administrative capability builds. <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> bypassed bloated cascading stylesheets applying exact aesthetic parameters universally building optimized output bundles directly. <strong>Axios</strong> was included substituting generic fetch functions exclusively processing structured interceptor capabilities dynamically automating standard JWT authorization header assignments universally executing secure traffic cleanly natively.</p>

<h2>4.6 Special Logic and System Automations</h2>

<h3>4.6.1 Order Preparation Guardrails</h3>
<p>The backend logic implements strict operational states. Orders originate explicitly flagged as ‘NEW’. Programmatically the system isolates the ‘Status’ function; administrators cannot force transitions mutating operational variables activating ‘PREPARING’ status pipelines absent verifying linked payment dependencies strictly identifying active 30% advanced deposit configurations executing logically generating hard denial blocks neutralizing operational cost losses automatically.</p>

<h3>4.6.2 Variant Matrix Pricing Engine</h3>
<p>Substituting individual cost assignments the system applies mathematical matrix parsings dynamically executing: `Price = (Base Cost * Size Parameter) + Active Flavor Modifiers`. Executing alterations within a single flavor row automatically distributes exact respective numerical pricing changes propagating structurally to all interconnected product configurations inherently.</p>

<h3>4.6.3 Financial Cashbook Rollover</h3>
<p>The daily cash ledger establishes strict accounting operations autonomously accumulating verified transaction values applying specific 'Income' allocations explicitly formulating the overall numeric arrays calculating exact 'Closing Balances'. Traversing absolute midnight intervals prompts automated cyclic behaviors migrating definitive closing calculations generating the absolute consecutive daily 'Opening Balance' securely rendering sequential tracking continuity immutably preventing financial analytical drift intrinsically.</p>

<h3>4.6.4 Automated Delivery Reminders — node-cron</h3>
<p>Functioning identically against manual administrative monitoring dependencies a background node-cron sequence processes active loops precisely scheduling daily triggers simultaneously operating exactly 08:00 AM intervals examining chronometric differential datasets targeting particular unfinalized bulk/custom order events residing strictly 48 hours structurally previous towards identified shipment periods executing background notification dispatches issuing explicitly 'Final Warning' emails alerting users regarding design parameter immutability natively executing independent intelligent cyclic automations robustly.</p>

<h3>4.6.5 Loyalty Points Redemption Cap</h3>
<p>Points compile fractionally processing verified carts allocating 1 point per 100 Rs transaction aggregates securely natively configuring database metrics actively. Reversing functionality processes redemption arrays isolating backend calculation validations completely evaluating checkout configurations denying arbitrary executions explicitly redeeming numeric point conversions structurally calculating any value functionally exceeding generic 30% definitive cart ceiling restrictions implicitly standardizing enterprise profit security unconditionally.</p>

